Phi — Licensing

Copyright (c) 2026 Daniel Ellison

This repository contains three kinds of thing, licensed accordingly.

1. THE LANGUAGE ITSELF IS FREE.

   The Phi language — its words, sounds, spellings, and grammar, as a
   system — is free for anyone to use, speak, write, teach, and build
   on, forever, no permission needed. Write your poems, courses,
   stories, and software in Phi; they are yours. No license in this
   repository restricts, or could restrict, the use of the language
   itself.

2. CODE — Apache License 2.0.

   The software in this repository — everything under scripts/ and
   web/ (excluding the fonts, see below), and the workflow files under
   .github/ — is licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.
   Full text: LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt

3. CONTENT — Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0
   International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0).

   Everything else — the lexicon entries (vocabulary/), the manual
   (manual/), the primer (primer/), the texts (texts/), the pamphlets
   (pamphlets/), the invitation (kia.md), the specification and
   philosophy documents (documents/), the archive (archive/), and the
   remaining prose of this repository — is licensed under
   CC BY-NC-SA 4.0: share and adapt freely, with attribution, for
   noncommercial purposes, keeping derivatives under the same license.
   Commercial use requires separate permission from the copyright
   holder. Full text: LICENSES/CC-BY-NC-SA-4.0.txt

FONTS. The font files under web/fonts/ are third-party works under the
SIL Open Font License 1.1; see the OFL-*.txt files alongside them. The
Tengwar Telcontar font under writing_systems/fonts/, used only to
generate the Tengwar glyph outlines in writing_systems/tengwar_glyphs.json,
is a third-party work by Johan Winge (freetengwar.sourceforge.net)
under the GNU General Public License; see the font's own name table
for its license statement.
